<p>George Sicherman, of <a href="https://www.futilitycloset.com/2012/07/25/sicherman-dice/">Sicherman dice</a> fame, has designed a puzzle to welcome the new year: <a href="https://sicherman.net/2026/index.html">Print out the PDF</a>, cut out the letters MMXXVI (the Roman numerals for 2026), and fit them into the tray provided so that no pieces with the same shape touch one another.</p>
<p>Sicherman&#8217;s website has <a href="https://sicherman.net/puzz.html">a whole range of puzzles</a>, most of them geometric.</p>
<p>(Thanks, William.)</p>
